uilder - A tool designed to assist students in planning their academic schedule. Visual Schedule Builder allows students to graphically view schedule options based on the courses and offering times that works best for them. For additional information please read the help documentation. Click here for information for the Spring semester 8 Week Sessions. Spring Registration Schedule Summary Registration Period Who is Eligible | Dates Payment Deadline Registration Continuing students (enrolled Spring, Summer, and/or Fall 2016). 5:00 p.m. January 5 for registration as of 4:30 p.m., January 5 Honors College / TAMS 7:00 a.m., Mon, Oct 3 - 4:30 p.m., Thur, Jan 5 Graduate Students 7:00 a.m., Mon, Oct 3 - 4:30 p.m., Thur, Jan 5 (for Regular and 8W1 session graduate courses) Seniors 7:00 a.m., Mon, Oct 10 - 4:30 p.m., Thurs, Jan 5 Juniors 7:00 a.m., Mon, Oct 17 - 4:30 p.m., Thurs, Jan 5 Graduate Students 7:00 a.m., Mon, Oct 17 - 4:30 p.m., Thurs, Jan 5 (for undergraduate courses) Sophomores 7:00 a.m., Mon, Oct 24 - 4:30 p.m., Thurs, Jan 5 Freshmen 7:00 a.m., Mon, Oct 31 - 4:30 p.m., Thurs, Jan 5 ALL eligible students Fri, Jan 6 -                        5:30 p.m., Thurs, Jan 12 6:00 p.m. January 12 for registration as of 5:30 p.m. January 12 Graduate Students October 3 - 11:30 a.m., March 17 (for 8W2 session graduate courses) 12:00 p.m. March 17 for registration as of 11:30 a.m. March 17 Late Registration Students who have not registered. 7:00 a.m., Jan 13 - 5:30 p.m., Jan 18 A $50 late fee is charged. Same day of registration by 6:00 p.m. Add/Drop Students who have registered and completed fee payment. 7:00 a.m., Jan 13 - 4:30 p.m., Jan 20 Last day to add a Spring class is January 20 at 4:30 p.m. 5:00 p.m., January 20 Spring 2017 Important Deadlines Deadline Regular Academic Session 8W1 8W2 Martin Luther King Day. Jan 16 Jan 16 N/A Classes Begin. Jan 17 Jan 17 Mar 20 Census. Jan 30 Jan 24 Mar 27 Beginning this date a student who wishes to drop a course must first receive written consent of the instructor. Jan 31 Jan 25 Mar 28 Last day for student to receive automatic grade of W for nonattendance. Last day for change in pass/no pass status. Last day to drop a course or withdraw from the semester with a grade of W for courses that the student is not passing. After this date, a grade of WF may be recorded. Feb 24 Feb 3 Apr 7 Beginning this date instructors may drop students with a grade of WF for nonattendance. Feb 25 Feb 4 Apr 8 Spring Break. Mar 13 - 19 N/A N/A Last day to drop with either W or WF. Last day for a student to drop a course with consent of the instructor. Apr 4 Feb 24 Apr 28 Beginning this date, a student who qualifies may request an Incomplete, with a grade of I. Apr 17 Feb 20 Apr 24 Last day to Withdraw (drop all classes). Last day for an instructor to drop a student with a grade of WF for nonattendance. Apr 21 Mar 3 May 5 Pre-Finals Days. May 3 - 4 N/A N/A Last Class Day. May 4 Mar 9 May 12 Reading Day (no classes). May 5 N/A May 5 Final Exams. May 6 - 12 Mar 10 May 12 End of session. May 12 Mar 10 May 12 Additional Resources For more information, contact the Registrar's Information Counter by calling 940-565-2111 or visiting Eagle Student Services Center (ESSC) Room 147. For instructions on using the myUNT Student Center for Registration, please visit Student Center Help.   Registration Info Find Classes Get Advised   Registration GuidesSpring 2017 Summer 2017 Fall 2017 Academic Catalog View All Forms Instructions for using MyUNT and EIS   Contact Information: Office of the Registrar 1155 Union Circle #311400 Denton, TX 76203-1400 USA Voice: 940-565-2111 Visit Us: Eagle Student Services Building http://registrar.unt.edu/ Email us: Have questions on content or technical issues? Please contact us. registrar@unt.edu UNT System: UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on: April 19, 2017 Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online | Emergen